data.title: TJX stock rises after Q4 beat, analysts praise 'MarMaxx strength'. Total sales: $17.7B, up 8.5% YoY. Comps grew 5%.
data.description: The stock prices for TJX Companies Inc (NYSE: TJX) surged in early trading following the release of strong fourth-quarter results. Analyst Robert Drbul from BTIG reaffirmed a Buy rating and raised the price target from $165 to $185, while Dana Telsey of Telsey Advisory Group reiterated an Outperform rating and increased the price target from $170 to $175. According to Drbul, TJX reported total sales of $17.7 billion, marking an 8.5% increase compared to the previous year, surpassing the 4.2% estimated growth. The company's total comparable sales rose by 5%, exceeding the 3% expectation, driven by growth in both traffic and ticket sales. For more analyst insights, refer to BTIG. This information and more can be found in the complete article on Benzinga.com.

data.title: AI-RAN Alliance hits key milestone with 132 members & new board members Qualcomm, SK Telecom, Vodafone to accelerate AI-native RAN innovation.
data.description: A significant advancement was revealed today by the AI-RAN Alliance, headquartered in Wakefield, Mass., as the organization declared a substantial increase in membership, now standing at 132 members worldwide. Noteworthy additions to the Board include technology giants Qualcomm, SK Telecom, and Vodafone. The primary focus remains on fast-tracking the implementation of AI-native Radio Access Network (RAN) solutions on a global level. As part of these efforts, the Alliance is gearing up to showcase 33 cutting-edge AI-powered innovations at MWC 2026. Additionally, four fresh industry blueprints are set to be unveiled at the event, demonstrating the seamless integration of AI within RAN technology to elevate wireless networks.

data.title: Gabriels Technology launches website for Anne Erwin Sotheby's Realty, powered by new tools. Prestigious firm in New England.
data.description: On February 26, 2026, in New York, Gabriels Technology Solutions revealed the revamped digital platform for Anne Erwin Sotheby's International Realty. The real estate firm, renowned in coastal New England for its luxury properties, has undergone a significant digital transformation. This redesign aims to enhance user experience on their website and improve accessibility to their prestigious listings. This update signifies a milestone in bridging technology and real estate, catering to the growing digital demands of the industry.
